comments.body:
Thanks for the patch, [~miklos.szegedi@cloudera.com]! Some comments:
# Is these code in {{recordUsage()}} inconsistent with your change?
{code}
float cpuUsagePercentPerCore = pTree.getCpuUsagePercent();
      float cpuUsageTotalCoresPercentage = cpuUsagePercentPerCore /
              resourceCalculatorPlugin.getNumProcessors();
{code}
# suggest to rename cpuUsagePercentPerCore to cpuUsagePercent if it isn't for cpu usage per core.
# fix the style issue reported by Hadoop QA
# suggest to add one empty line before {{changeContainerResource(containerId, changeEvent.getResource());}}

Patch looks good. Only one nit, this comments should be rewrite.
{code}
            // if machine has 6 cores and 3 are used,
            // cpuUsagePercentPerCore should be 300% and
            // cpuUsageTotalCoresPercentage should be 50%
{code}
